# CrewRules™ Feature Status Badges — UI Standard

Feature status badges communicate maturity of tools and features. Use consistently across the platform.

## Mandatory Requirements

- **Always use the exact approved class strings** for feature status badges unless explicitly told otherwise. Do not substitute, shorten, or alter the Tailwind classes.
- **Never use amber/gold for feature status badges.** That color is reserved exclusively for CrewRules™ PRO features.

## Badge Types

### BETA
Feature works but is still being tested and improved. Use for: functional features still evolving, features where feedback is being gathered (e.g. Commute Assist 2-Leg, Weather Brief, Mentorship platform).

```tsx
<span className="inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold bg-fuchsia-500/20 text-fuchsia-400 border border-fuchsia-500/40">
  BETA
</span>
```

### IN DEVELOPMENT
Feature UI may exist but functionality is not active yet. Use for: upcoming features not yet connected to backend logic, early UI previews (e.g. Family View™).

```tsx
<span className="bg-cyan-500/20 text-cyan-200 border border-cyan-400/40 text-xs font-semibold px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">
  IN DEVELOPMENT
</span>
```

## Standard JSX Usage

Use these exact snippets when adding feature badges.

BETA example:

```tsx
<span className="inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold bg-fuchsia-500/20 text-fuchsia-400 border border-fuchsia-500/40">
  BETA
</span>
```

IN DEVELOPMENT example:

```tsx
<span className="bg-cyan-500/20 text-cyan-200 border border-cyan-400/40 text-xs font-semibold px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">
  IN DEVELOPMENT
</span>
```

Place feature badges to the right of the section title in the same flex row using gap-2 or gap-3.

## Rules

- Keep badge text short: `BETA`, `IN DEVELOPMENT`
- All feature badges use pill style (`rounded-full`)
- Use the same badge styles everywhere for consistency
